### Description

```ts
@Directive({
  selector: '[standalone]',
  standalone: true,
})
export class StandaloneDirective {
  @Input()
  set standalone(value: any) {
    // ...
  }
}

@Directive({
  selector: '[app-child]',
  hostDirectives: [
    {
      directive: StandaloneDirective,
      inputs: ['standalone: alias']
      /*
        Work:
        <div app-child alias="...

        Don't work, Error: NG0309
        <div app-child standalone="...
      */
    },
  ],
})
export class ChildDirective {}
```

This makes it impossible to have a single api when there is a single implementation. If both (standalone directive and component where it's provided) exposed, it adds misunderstanding where and which (alias or real name) should be used.

Looks like in this case when the directive is already applied in code we can skip second applying and just pass the input value.

